news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' net profit dips 65.49% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Suraj Estate Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 106.14 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 66.05 per cent from Rs 312.66 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: UP RERA starts pre-hearing scrutiny of complaints to help homebuyers
news.para: In doing so, UP RERA not only simplified the process of filing of complaints, but made it more comprehensive also, it said in a statement. "Now the process has become more user-friendly and will be conducive to early listing and speedy disposal of complaints.

news.title: Commercial property prices in German drop by 12.1 % in Q4 2023
news.para: For the full year, commercial real estate prices dropped 10.2%, accelerating their decline after small drops of less than one percent in 2022 and 2021, VDP's data showed.

news.title: Bhubaneshwar civic body to collect holding tax from buildings on Idco land
news.para: The civic body was not empowered to collect holding tax from such establishments till the last financial year as buildings that came up on Idco land were getting basic facilities like drains, road and streetlights from Idco.

news.title: Tritax Big Box agrees on possible $1.17 billion offer for UK Commercial Property REIT
news.para: Under the terms of the possible deal, every UKCM owner will get 0.444 new Tritax shares for each share they hold. The companies are poised to have a combined market capitalization of 3.9 billion pounds.

news.title: Arihant Superstructures' net profit declines 21.77% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Arihant Superstructures' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 119.46 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 3.70 per cent from Rs 115.20 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Rajasthan housing department to finalise alignment for Jaipur metro line-II extension
news.para: On Thursday, deputy chief minister and finance minister Diya Kumari in the interim Budget announced extension of the proposed Line 2 of Jaipur Metro from Ambabari to Vidhyadhar Nagar.

news.title: Old Ahmedabad still has highest density of commercial properties
news.para: Spread over 481 sq km, Ahmedabad city has an overall property density of 5,087 units per sq km.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to offer upto 40% rebate on pending dues of builders to revive stalled projects
news.para: The Greater Noida Authority has proposed a one-time settlement scheme offering up to a 40% discount on pending dues of builders. The rebate applies to outstanding dues until March 31, 2023, with a 40% discount for payments made by January 31, 2024.

news.title: Cera Sanitaryware's net profit dips 9.42% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Cera Sanitaryware's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 454.89 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 3.42 per cent from Rs 470.99 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Survey to install UID number plates in Ludhiana moving at snail's pace
news.para: The officials blamed poor support from public for the slow pace. They said the residents refuse to give information to the private contractor’s team.

news.title: Land survey to be conducted on pilot basis: Mangaluru deputy commissioner
news.para: As many as 228 applications were submitted to various departments during the gram vastavya programme. Villagers of Kalmakaru brought to the notice of officials that nine families, who lost their properties in natural calamities, have not been provided alternative sites.

news.title: Kapil Dev buys 16-acre land in Karjat for Rs 8 crore
news.para: The land spread on both sides of the road is located around 500 metres away from Kothimbe village and much ahead of the tourist hotspot Solanpada dam.

news.title: Student accommodation platform Amber raises $21 million led by Gaja Capital
news.para: Founded in 2017 by Goel and Madhur Gujar, Amber primarily focuses on Indians studying abroad in markets like the US, the UK, Ireland, Australia and Canada, as the student accommodation in these countries is worth $60 billion, Goel said.

news.title: NCLT dismisses plea against Pancard Clubs resolution plan
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) dismissed Ashdan Properties' petition against Chemhub Tradelink's approved resolution plan for Pancard Clubs, a bankrupt entity with over 1.5 million timeshare subscribers. Ashdan was one of three bidders interested in acquiring Pancard.

news.title: Dues cleared, 13 years gone, no handover of homes yet: Tashee Capital Gateway buyers
news.para: The project was later taken over under the SWAMIH scheme in Oct 2022. Despite the handover, the project’s progress remains sluggish, much to the frustration of homebuyers.

news.title: Gurugram: Project held up, Mahira Homes' buyers seek temporary accommodation or rent
news.para: Though the project’s licence was restored in September, the developer has failed to resume work, with only 60% work completed since its inception.

news.title: Adani Realty and L&T Realty strong contenders for 24-acre Bandra reclamation plot
news.para: The third bidder is Mumbai-based Mayfair Housing, but sources said it is not certain whether it will meet the stringent criteria in the tender document.

news.title: Soon, Panvel civic body to act against property tax defaulters
news.para: According to municipal commissioner Ganesh Deshmukh, the civic body will go on a spree to seize the properties of the defaulters soon.

news.title: Government asks Odisha RERA to waive off registration fee for BDA project
news.para: In a letter to ORERA chairman, director (housing) Debasish Singh said BDA has submitted the application along with requisite documents for exemption of registration and late registration fees for the project.
